The andvari SERVER (everything under this `server/` directory) is licensed to you
under the GNU Affero General Public License, version 3 or (at your option) any
later version, as published by the Free Software Foundation.

The Affero license is deliberate (F1, docs/design/2026-07-16-trust-attestation-
strategy.md): andvari's server is offered over a network, and AGPLv3 §13 ("Remote
Network Interaction") requires that anyone who runs a modified andvari server as a
network service make the modified source available to that service's users. This is
a security property, not just a licensing preference — it keeps the code a household
or a stranger actually runs auditable. (The client apps/extension/web are GPLv3 — see
the repository-root LICENSE and LICENSING.md.)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ⚠️  CANONICAL LICENSE TEXT REQUIRED BEFORE PUBLISHING — one manual step.

  The verbatim GNU AGPLv3 text was not available in the offline environment that
  scaffolded this file (only GPLv3 ships in Debian's common-licenses). A legal
  license grant needs the FULL, byte-exact FSF text — do NOT hand-transcribe it.

  Before flipping the repository public, replace THIS boxed notice with the exact
  contents of:

        https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.txt

  e.g.  `curl -o server/LICENSE.body https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.txt`
        then splice its body in here (keep the SPDX line at the very top).

  Until then the grant above stands by reference to the FSF-published AGPL-3.0-or-later.
